			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	<u>About Undercurrent:</u> Undercurrent applies a digital worldview to business strategy&mdash;focusing on transformation across the enterprise, enabling businesses to create durable competitive advantage. Since 2007, Undercurrent has focused on developing strategies that help clients outperform the market by harnessing the disruptive power of digital.</p>
<p>
	<u>About the Role: </u>Candidates looking for a corner office need not apply. Our ideal team member is not only brilliant, persuasive, and personable, but also genuine, disciplined, and loyal. In our company culture, sales is a dirty word. This role represents a new approach to sales in a consultative environment, where the Opportunity Manager will flank an entire team of Strategy Directors who are already have an active business development process. This role is responsible for optimizing the business development process and collaborating with the directors to reduce their workload while ensuring the timely delivery of proposals.</p>
<p>
	<u>Responsibilities:</u></p>
<p>
	Opportunity Management<br />
	★ Attend new business meetings with Undercurrent&rsquo;s directors and aid in the business development process<br />
	★ Develop scopes of work based on input from the directors<br />
	★ Assist in ongoing communications and followup with current leads<br />
	★ Assist in the legal negotiation of scopes and contracts<br />
	★ Assist in the ongoing evolution of the Undercurrent service offering</p>
<p>
	Pipeline Management<br />
	★ Keep Undercurrent&rsquo;s CRM/pipeline tool up to date and prioritized<br />
	★ Manage the ebb and flow of incoming opportunities to match with available resources<br />
	★ Manage and evolve Undercurrent&rsquo;s proprietary system for resource planning (Fretboard)<br />
	★ Develop short and long term business development strategy by company, by vertical, and by service<br />
	★ Deliver performance reports in partnership with Undercurrent&rsquo;s finance director</p>
<p>
	<u>Experience:</u></p>
<p>
	The Opportunity Manager is a new role for Undercurrent, and the candidate that is awarded the job will be one interested in getting in at the early stages of a rapidly growing company with a four year track record of success. He/ she has experience as a sales manager, account manager, business development leader, or equivalent, with a minimum of 5 years in a people-driven business. That business may be an agency, consultancy, or firm of any shape and size. He/she will lead business development on behalf of the company. This position reports to the Operations Director.</p>
<p>
	For more information, please contact love@undercurrent.com.&nbsp;</p>
]]></description>
